//! Conformance Layer 3 — ferrotorch-jit graph IR, trace, symbolic, and codegen_ir (C7.1).
//!
//! Tracking issue: #806 (C7.1 graph+tracing conformance)
//! Reference: torch == 2.11.0 (torch.jit.trace + torch.fx + torch.export semantics)
//!
//! Fixtures: tests/conformance/fixtures_graph.json
//! Generated by: scripts/regenerate_jit_fixtures.py
//!
//! ## Coverage
//!
//! ### graph.rs
//! - [`IrGraph`] construction, node/value counts, input/output lists
//! - [`IrGraph::topological_order`] invariant (producers before consumers)
//! - [`IrGraph::is_constant`] distinguishes constants from inputs
//! - [`IrGraph::remove_node`] decrements node and value counts
//! - [`Dtype`] name + from_type_name round-trip
//! - Default F32 and explicit F64 dtype propagation
//!
//! ### trace.rs
//! - [`trace`] graph structure for x+x, relu(x*y), mm(A,B).sum()
//! - `trace` with `requires_grad=false` returns an error containing "no grad_fn"
//! - `trace` topological order is valid on the produced graph
//!
//! ### symbolic.rs
//! - [`Guard`] accepts / rejects inputs per symbolic vs concrete dims
//! - [`Guard`] enforces min/max range on symbolic dims
//! - [`patch_reshape_for_symbolic_dims`] rewrites single-match reshape targets
//! - Ambiguous reshape target (value appears twice) is left unchanged
//!
//! ### codegen_ir.rs
//! - [`lower_to_loops`]: Neg, Add → single flat loop
//! - [`lower_to_loops`]: Sum, Mean, Prod → accumulator pattern
//! - [`lower_to_loops`]: fused [Neg, Relu, Sigmoid] → single loop with 6-stmt body
//! - [`lower_matmul`]: triple-nested i,j,k loop
//! - [`apply_op_expr`]: Pow → FnCall("powf", [...])
//! - Op classification: `is_unary_elementwise`, `is_binary_elementwise`, `is_reduction`
//!
//! ## Layer 4
//! Surface-coverage gate is deferred to C7.4 wrap-up.
//!
//! ## cascade_skip convention
//! `cascade_skip!(label, issue)` prints a diagnostic and returns early.
//! This is NOT `#[ignore]` — the test runs and emits the notice so CI
//! counts skips separately from passes.

#![allow(
    clippy::cast_possible_truncation,
    clippy::cast_precision_loss,
    clippy::cast_sign_loss,
    clippy::uninlined_format_args,
    clippy::explicit_iter_loop
)]

